Wild animals from one part of the world being exposed by viruses/bacteria/etc from wild animals from a completely other part of the world is just set up for potentional disaster.

snippet.textDisplay: It was named seafood market but in reality they were selling wild animals. Yup typical chinese. Animals that other civilised people wouldnt dare to eat : bats, pangolin, dogs, monkeys etc. Things worsened as the market not only stock live animals but also processed them in the same vicinity with a very low hygiene. It was the chinese new year season and as demand for these illegal animals  increased people flocked the market. Virus in some way jumped into humans.
